solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    bool canBeEqual(vector<int>& target, vector<int>& arr) {
        if (target.size() != arr.size()) return false;
        int freq[1001] = {0};
        for (int x : target) ++freq[x];
        for (int x : arr) --freq[x];
        for (int i = 1; i <= 1000; ++i)
            if (freq[i] != 0) return false;
        return true;
    }
};```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Any permutation can be reached by a sequence of subarray reversals, so the problem reduces to checking whether the multisets of elements match. A frequency array of size 1001 (given the value range) counts occurrences in O(n) time and O(1) extra space.

